5000|$|A five-official {{system is}} used in arena football, most high school varsity football, and in most semi-pro games. It adds the back judge to the four-official system. In five-man high school crews, the {{linesman}} {{is responsible for the}} chain crew, the line judge is the official timekeeper of the game, and the back judge times the play clock and the one minute allowed for <b>time-outs</b> (only 30 seconds are allowed during team <b>time-outs</b> during televised college games to reduce time).|$|R
